# Backend Architecture

The backend is a **modular monolith** built with **Clean Architecture** and Clean Code.
Java + Spring Boot. Base package: `com.nitxrealm` (no hyphen — Java packages cannot contain `-`).

## Module organization

Code is organized by **business module** (bounded context), not by technical layer at the top.
Each module is self-contained and owns its full vertical slice.

```
backend/src/main/java/com/nitxrealm/
├── NitxRealmApplication.java
└── {module-name}/              # e.g. user, billing, catalog
    ├── domain/
    ├── application/
    ├── infrastructure/
    └── presentation/
```

## Layers (inside each module)

| Layer | Responsibility | Knows about |
|-------|----------------|-------------|
| `domain` | Pure business model & rules. No frameworks. | nothing (innermost) |
| `application` | Use cases orchestrating domain. Defines ports (interfaces) it needs. | `domain` |
| `infrastructure` | Adapters: DB, email, security, messaging. Implements ports. | `domain`, `application` |
| `presentation` | Entry points: REST controllers, request/response DTOs. | `application` |

## The Dependency Rule (most important)

Dependencies always point **inward**. Outer layers depend on inner layers, never the reverse.

```
presentation ─┐
              ├──► application ──► domain
infrastructure┘
```

- `domain` MUST NOT import `application`, `infrastructure`, `presentation`, or any framework (no Spring, no JPA, no Jackson).
- `application` MUST NOT import `infrastructure` or `presentation`. It depends on **interfaces** (ports) it declares in `domain`/`application`.
- `infrastructure` and `presentation` depend inward and wire concrete implementations.

```java
// ❌ BAD: domain depends on a framework / outer layer
package com.nitxrealm.user.domain.model;
import jakarta.persistence.Entity;        // infra concern leaking into domain
import com.nitxrealm.user.infrastructure.persistence.JpaUserEntity;

// ✅ GOOD: domain is pure
package com.nitxrealm.user.domain.model;
public final class User { /* business rules only */ }
```

## Cross-module communication

- Modules talk through **public application use cases** or **domain events**, never by reaching into another module's `infrastructure` or `domain.model` internals.
- Prefer asynchronous **domain events** for decoupling (see `application.mdc` handlers + `infrastructure` event publisher).
- No shared mutable state between modules.

## Layer-specific rules

See the focused rules for each concern: `domain.mdc`, `application.mdc`,
`infrastructure.mdc`, `persistence.mdc`, `presentation.mdc`, `spring-boot.mdc`,
`clean-code.mdc`, `tests.mdc`.
